<br>
I had 2 kodiaks on me while Gala and my pet ( <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) took the other one. Where the third one came from, only the Gods know, but soon i was taking 20 dmg a pop from both. I was hurting to say the least. Well, from out of nowhere, this ranger comes along and jumps in without hesitation! He pulled 1 kodiak off me so I could finish the other with Gala's alt's help and my pets. He did this without regard for his own life and with the possibility of death hanging over him as well.<br>
<br>
If you see Dougen &lt;Bloodsong&gt;, send him a tell or say hi to him, he is indeed a kind soul in an otherwise cruel world<br>
<br>
Dougen <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ... a good person... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/beverquestersofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=galadriaculravenni>Galadria Culravenni</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 261<br> <font color=#8B4513>(5/31/01 3:54:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A diamond in the ruff.. err.. rough...</span><hr size=1> Aye, verily, Dougen was a literal life-saver that night. He stuck around long enough to chat a little with us, to bestow some heals and buffs upon my character at least, and to sit with Ordained's alt when I had to camp to reset the DSL (because Raynn was online at the same time elsewhere).<br>
<br>
Then when our chars waved goodbye and went on a bit further and pulled a lion to kill and suddenly found ourselves beset by a lioness and a shadow wolf and another kodiak all at the same time, Dougen once more appeared on the scene to watch over us and make sure we were all right!<br>
